      "ai_insights": {
        "executive_summary": "CHC delivered mixed performance in February 2026, with a network-wide Performance Score average of 37.6 out of 100 (where 50 represents the network average), reflecting uneven operational discipline across five locations. While we see encouraging month-over-month gains in scheduler compliance and patient delays at Blue Pod and Muskegon, persistent overtime and patient wait times remain the primary operational headwinds. Three clinics\u2014LHCP, Blue Pod, and Muskegon\u2014continue to log 2\u20133 treatments past closing daily, signaling a systematic scheduling tension that warrants coordinated attention.",
        "highlights": [
          "Blue Pod has demonstrated meaningful month-over-month improvement, with average delay declining from 43.6 minutes in January to 38.9 minutes in February, a 10.8% reduction that brings the clinic closer to operational health despite remaining 72% above the company average delay of 22.6 minutes. Muskegon's scheduler compliance rose from 61.1% in January to 70.6% in February, a 15.6% gain that reflects stronger adherence to iOptimize recommendations; notably, this clinic also achieved 100% iAssign Utilization and maintains the lowest average delay in the network at 10.6 minutes. Red Pod continues to stand out with a Performance Score of 53 (above the 50-point network average) and chair utilization of 86.9%, which is 1.8 standard deviations above the clinic group mean of 72.3%, demonstrating how disciplined scheduling can drive asset efficiency."
        ],
        "concerns": [
          "We noticed that Muskegon, despite strong compliance and delay metrics, is experiencing a consistent decline in chair utilization over the past two months (from approximately 81.3% in the three-month average down to 75.8% in February, R\u00b2=0.78) and declining nurse utilization (three-month average of 78.5%, R\u00b2=0.61). This pattern warrants exploration to clarify whether workflow changes, staffing constraints, or volume fluctuations are at play. LHCP remains the lowest performer by composite score (21 out of 100) and continues to log 2.3 treatments past closing daily, alongside a three-month average of 39.2 minutes overtime per patient (R\u00b2=0.85), suggesting that scheduling templates or nurse-to-chair assignments may be misaligned with actual patient flow and capacity."
        ],
        "recommendations": [
          "Blue Pod's average patient delay of 38.9 minutes represents the most pressing operational gap in the network\u201473% above the company average of 22.6 minutes\u2014and directly undercuts the patient experience we aim to deliver. We recommend scheduling a focused review of Blue Pod's appointment templates and nurse-to-chair assignment protocols to identify friction points; alongside this, we suggest piloting a brief iAssign training refresher with the scheduling team to strengthen real-time adoption. This targeted intervention, paired with monthly check-ins, should clarify whether the clinic's recent 10.8% improvement in January-to-February delays is the beginning of a sustained trend."
        ]
      }
